 <!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
 <!--  Introduction -->
 <!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     The Class application module supports the definition of a class or set. A
     class or set may be:
   </p>

   <ul>
     <li>
       <p>class by extension</p>
       <p>a class that is define by specifying a criterion for membership,
       which does not enumerate the members</p>
     </li>

     <li>
       class by intension
       <p>a class that is defined by enumerating its members.</p>
     </li>
   </ul>
   <note>
     This module can be used in combination with another
     module, such as Product view definition, in order to indicate that
     a Product view definition is a class.
   </note>
   
   <p> 
   In the ARM of the combined module, an application object is created,
   which is both a 
   <module_ref linkend="product_view_definition:1_outscope">
     <b>product_view_definition</b>
   </module_ref> and a <b>class</b>. This
   application object inherits from <b>class</b> the following
   capabilities: 
 </p>
 <ul>
   <li> 
   involvement in set theory relationships, such as union and
   intersection;  
 </li>
 <li>
   specification an individual member by a classification
   relationship; and  
 </li>
 <li>enumeration of the complete membership.</li>
</ul>
 </purpose>

  <!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
 <!--  In scope statement -->
 <!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
 <inscope>
 </inscope>

 <!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
 <!--  Out of scope statement -->
 <!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
 <outscope>
   <li>classification and the specification of complete set membership;</li>
   <li>set theory relationships;
   <note>
     Set theory relationships are within the scope of the
     <module_ref linkend="set_theory:introduction">set_theory</module_ref> application
     module. 
   </note>
 </li>
 <li>mappings between sets or classes;</li>
 <li>relationships that are not set theory relationships.</li>
 </outscope>

